ssful `Class.forName` invocation be optimized by Graal or JIT? It seems not. I could update to use `MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class)`, but it returns a raw Class. It's alright, I guess. Maybe the `MethodHandle` call isn't counted due to line coverage; however, it mentions dynamic access coverage, which is interesting.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method access**\\n\\nI’m thinking that the signature is `(String)Class` because the cast context `Class<?>` erases to `Class`. That makes sense. However, I wonder if the Native image can't access `privateLookupIn` for a package-private method without metadata, which could cause the test to fail and result in no coverage. But doesn’t the JVM agent need to run first? If the test fails, then maybe that's why there's no coverage. It’s a bit complicated!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_kkH57lrGwgooxvDeYzSV9kIX|fc_0eb8e487ddfa44ee016a00743cc0e08192ad6d2e7a1f12fb73", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/HeaderMatcherTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n\nimport static org.hamcrest.Matchers.equalTo;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\n\npublic class HeaderMatcherTest {\n    @Test\n    void resolvesCompilerGeneratedClassResolver() throws Throwable {\n        MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(\n                HeaderMatcher.class,\n                MethodHandles.lookup());\n        MethodHandle classResolver = lookup.findStatic(\n                HeaderMatcher.class,\n                \"class$\",\n                MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = (Class<?>) classResolver.invokeExact(\n                \"io.restassured.assertion.HeaderMatcher\");\n\n        assertSame(HeaderMatcher.class, resolvedClass);\n    }\n", "newText": "import static org.hamcrest.Matchers.equalTo;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\n\npublic class HeaderMatcherTest {\n    @Test\n    void resolvesCompilerGeneratedClassResolverThroughGroovyDispatch() {\n        HeaderMatcher matcher = new HeaderMatcher();\n\n        Object resolvedClass = matcher.this$dist$invoke$1(\n                \"class$\",\n                new Object[] {\"io.restassured.assertion.HeaderMatcher\"});\n\n        assertSame(HeaderMatcher.class, resolvedClass);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 817, "output": 3960, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32425, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778414599983, "responseId": "resp_0eb8e487ddfa44ee016a00740898a48192817fc99a588eacc7"}}
